beer_brewer_name: Tradin pivovar v Rakovnku - Pivovar Rakovnk
review_blob: Light brown color with a nice head. Aroma a bit sweet, with notes of caramel and brown sugar or light molasses. Taste light and a bit sweet. Grainy with caramel and toast.
beer_name: Bakal Polotmav / ezan Vepn 11 (Light Dark Beer)

beer_brewer_name: Tradin pivovar v Rakovnku - Pivovar Rakovnk
review_blob: UPDATED: APR 27, 2016

beer_brewer_name: Tradin pivovar v Rakovnku - Pivovar Rakovnk
review_blob: Clear golden color with a nice foamy white head. Aroma grainy and grassy, with a vegetative note. Taste bitter and vegetative. Not very good.
Clear copper color with a bit of a head. Aroma sweet, with notes of caramel, raisins, and plums. Taste sweet, with notes of plums and raisin. Some not very good aftertaste though.
Golden color with smallish head. Aroma grainy with a touch of caramel. Taste grainy, bready, a touch sweet. Low carbonation. Not bad
Dark mahogany with nice head. Aroma has nice coffee and vanilla notes. Taste is roasty, with coffee and vanilla as well. Very flavorful fur the style.

Clear copper color with nice head. Aroma quite sweet (especially after youve been drinking Czech Pilsner fit a week!) with some bubblegum notes. Taste sweet, bubblegumy, with just a bit of hop character.
Bit hazy, golden with sticky head. Aroma grainy and clean. Taste as well. Very easy drinking.
Golden color with nice sticky head. Aroma grainy with a touch of caramel. Taste grainy, again with a touch of caramel. Decent

Black with nice tan head and ruby highlights. Aroma has a ton of vanilla, sweet notes and a bit of roast. Taste is a bit acrid with roast notes and a bit of sweetness. Not the best example of the style Ive ever tasted.
Hazy orange with no head. Aroma of smoked sausage and wood. Taste nicely Smokey, again the smoked sausage thing. Different.

Deep hazy honey color tinged with red. Aroma very faint. Wine grapes and berries mostly. Taste slightly tart. Not very sour at all, with a tannic palate. Lots of wine character and wood tannins. Interesting
Hazy gold with a foamy head that dissipates quickly. Aroma of pineapple and guava (but the actual fruit, not the hop version). Taste, well, rather like guava. Tart, but not really sour. Quite nice.
Black with ruby highlights and big head. Aroma bready and yeasty, with a surprising lack of roast character. Taste nice and roasty, clean and a bit biter. Nice.
Black with big tan head. Aroma of roast and chocolate, kinda subdued. Taste of roast and Tootsie rolls, write unusual, but nice.
Black with no head. Aroma of roast, chocolate, espresso, and more chocolate, very nice. Taste roasty and chocolaty, with some coffee and ash. Very nice
Black with a nice tan head. Aroma roasty with notes of chocolate, espresso, and vanilla. Taste roasty as well, with tastes of bitter chocolate, espresso, and chalk.
Golden color with white foamy head. Aroma is fairly off-putting, rotten egg mostly. Taste is similarly bad. One of the worse beers Ive had recently.
Hazy honey color with a foamy head. Aroma grainy, yeasty, with a hint of lemon. Taste grainy and yeasty, not as clean as most Czech lager, but thats to be expected. Nice
Clear golden color with a nice white head. Aroma grainy and clean. Taste grainy, with good bitterness and nice mouth feel. Good Czech Pilsner.
Clear golden color with a small head. Aroma grainy and sweet. Taste grainy and clean with a hint of bitterness. Nice, simple, and very drinkable.

Clear golden color with a nice white head. Aroma pungent, with garlic and onion notes. Not what youd expect from a galaxy beer. Taste bitter and with the same notes as the aroma. There ate some citrus notes there too, but you kinda have to look for them... Bit of a strange beer, though not necessarily bad.

Clear golden color with a nice white head. Aroma yeasty, bready, and grassy.
Taste bready, grassy, and slightly metallic. especially in aftertaste. Decent

Clear copper color with a nice white head. Aroma of citrus and tropical fruit. Taste nicely hoppy, with orange rind and marmalade notes. Lower carbonation helps keeps this nice and sessionable despite the abv.

Clear golden color with a nice foamy head. Aroma yeasty, bready, and smokey. Not as smokey as other offerings from this brewery. But it there. Taste bready, smokey, and a but metallic. As a Helles, its mediocre, since the smoke covers up the delicate flavors that distinguish a good Helles. As a smoked beer its ok - not as smokey as others, but I think thats an advantage.
Clear copper color with a off white head thats impassive at first but doesnt last very long. Aroma of honey, caramel, and a bit of veggie note. Taste is honey, veggies, and metal. Pretty awful

Clearish gold with a big orange-tinged white head. Aroma citrusy, flowery, and fruity,with notes of mango and pineapple. Taste has a lot of tropical flavors in it - pineapple, pappaya, mango, and very sweet oranges. Very yummy
beer_name: Boulevard Collaboration No. 5 Tropical Pale Ale

review_blob: Clear gold with a nice foamy head. Aroma bready and a little spicy, with yeast notes. Taste bready, yeasty, and smooth. A wonderful Czech pils
Black with a decent, but quickly disappearing, tan head. Aroma sweet and roasty, with a touch of ash. Taste... kinda watery, roasty, some chalk, light body.

Clearish copper color with an off-white head. Aroma piney and fruity. I didnt specifically get tropical or orange out of it, though. Taste has a good amount of fruit, and pineapple stands out. Nice beer

Clear golden color with a nice head. Aroma sweet and floral, with some pine notes. Taste clean and bitter, with some herbal notes and chalk (unusual in an IPA. Not necessarily bad, but unusual) Very easily drinkable, but a very bitter and not very flavorful palate make it harder to finish the bottle.
beer_name: Green Flash Segal Ranch Session IPA

review_blob: Clear straw with a big foamy head. Aroma fruity and big, with notes of citrus and melon. Taste of oranges and bread, very light. Somewhat high carbonation prevents this from being truly "chugable", but its still a very nice summer drink.

beer_brewer_name: Bernard Family Brewery / Rodinn pivovar Bernard
review_blob: Clear golden color with a nice white head. Aroma grainy, bready, and yeasty, with a touch of sulfur. Taste firmly bitter, clean, and bready, with a surprisingly full body for the style/abv. Very nice Czech Pilsner
beer_name: Bernard Svtl Lek 12 / Premium / Bohemian Lager

review_blob: Black with a nice mocha head. Aroma of coffee, whisky, and wood. Taste has a lot of peat in it, smoke, wood, coffee, whisky, and burnt notes. Basically this is one big smoke bomb. Great if you like the style, a bit tiring on the the palate if you dont.

Black with a nice mocha head. Aroma of roast and dark fruit. Taste of roast and bubblegum, coffee and chocolate notes develop later, but the bubblegum lingers to the the finish. Pity, because it could have been a great stout otherwise.
Almost colorless, very clear with no head. Aroma of Apple drink concentrate, green apples, and a touch of vinegar. Taste sweet, alcoholic, and a little bitter. Not very good.

Clear gold with a nice even head. Aroma fruity and floral, with some nice tropical notes. Taste has a tone of tropical fruit as well, papaya, mango, and some things I cant quite name but that you can imagine grow on tropical islands :). Very very nice IPA
Clearish gold with a nice head. Aroma grassy and piney. Taste bitter and clean, with high carbonation and piney notes.

Black with a very dark mocha head. Aroma of coffee, chocolate, alcohol, dark fruit, and notes of ash. Taste very full, dark and rich. Lots of coffee and chocolate notes, some licorice, some very dark caramel. The whole motif of this beer is "big and black" and it pulls it off very very well.
beer_name: To l Goliat Imperial Coffee Stout

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: 5% version. Greenish-yellow color with good fizz and just a bit of a head. Aroma of sour apple candy and alcohol. Taste dry and crisp, with some veggie notes and a bit of bitterness. Not very sweet, but kinda full.
Brown with ruby highlights and a mocha head. Aroma of roast and chocolate with some sweet notes and some ash. Taste roasty and dry, bitter chocolate, and espresso.

Clear mahogany with no head. Aroma very sweet, dark fruit, dark caramel, liquorice, hint of vanilla, and lots of alcohol. Taste of sweet dark fruit, plums, raisins, and rich dark caramel. Warm palate, great winter warmer. Drank this on January 1st on a cold day and it really hit the spot. Hint: scrape off the wax seal before uncorking this beer to avoid bits of wax in your glass.
Clear gold with nice foamy head. Aroma grainy and sweet, with a grassy note. Taste grainy and sweet, with a bit of corn note. Decent
Clear copper with off white head. Aroma spicy and earthy, with die caramel notes. Taste full and bitter, with some spruce notes, a little strange, but not bad for a DIPA

Hazy copper color with orange-tinged head. Aroma huge and flowery, grassy, and with some sweet caramel/toffee notes. Taste is big, bold, and bitter. The bitterness kinda hids more delicate flavors, which makes it hard to make them out, but I suppose this is part of the style. If you like DIPAs, youd like this one.

Hazy gold with a foamy white head. Aroma yeasty and bready, with maybe a touch of citrus rind. Taste bready and yeasty with a lemony taste mid palate and again in aftertaste. Pretty subtle, though it does come out more once beer warms a bit.

Clear brown with almost no head. Aroma of root beer, straight up. Taste, well... it tastes like root beer. I mean you almost cant tell theres alcohol in the thing except a touch of aftertaste and a bit of warmth in your stomach. I liked it a lot, but it tastes nothing like beer :)
beer_name: Small Town Not Your Fathers Root Beer (5.9%)

review_blob: Hazy golden color with a nice white head. Aroma of citrus and flowers, with some oxidation notes. Taste has a fair bit of grapefruit rind, good bitterness, a little bit of oxidation, and a good balance. I would venture a guess this beer is all of 35 IBUs or so, but for the ABV thats plenty. Good beer, I venture that is excellent fresh.

Black with a nice mocha head. Aroma sweet and roasty, with a strong wine/dark fruit component, maybe overripe cherry or plum. Taste roasty and full, lots of coffee and chocolate notes, less sweet than Aroma would suggest. Heavy for a porter, but quite good.

Hazy light gold with a big foamy head. Aroma wheaty, slightly sweet, bready, with notes of yeast and grass. Taste light, grassy, sweet, and grainy. This beer starts out promising on looks and aroma, but ends up disappointing on taste.
